                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6342.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Nogales</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A very bitter resentment here and in the State [of Sonora] resulting from the
                    killing of Madero. The State will not submit to the Provisional Government at
                    Mexico City.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowman</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
